081217232130/http://www.uefa.com/newsfiles/ucl/2005/1108503_fr.pdf| archivedate= 17 December 2008 | url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n'''Milan'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.squawka.com/news/ronaldinho-backs-napoli-to-stop-juventus-serie-a-dominance/998110#7l34FtFCyZhrYYMI.97|title=Ronaldinho backs Napoli to stop Juventus' Serie A dominance|publisher=www.squawka.com|author1=Jeorge Bird|date=10 October 2017|accessdate=15 January 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Serie A]]: [[2010\u201311 Serie A|2010\u201311]]\n\n'''Flamengo'''<ref name=\"Forbes\"/>\n* [[Campeonato Carioca de Futebol|Campeonato Carioca]]: [[2011 Campeonato Carioca|2011]]\n* [[Ta\u00e7a Guanabara]]: 2011\n* [[Ta\u00e7a Rio]]: 2011\n\n'''Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro'''<ref name=\"Forbes\">{{cite news |title=Ronaldinho Announces His Retirement; Why He Is One Of Soccer's All-Time Greats |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/bobbymcmahon/2018/01/16/ronaldinho-announces-his-retirement-why-he-is-one-of-soccers-all-time-greats/#649b1c56cff9 |accessdate=27 September 2018 |work=Forbes}}</ref>\n*[[Campeonato Mineiro]]: [[2013 Campeonato Mineiro|2013]]\n*[[Copa Libertadores]]: [[2013 Copa Libertadores|2013]]\n*[[Recopa Sudamericana]]: [[2014 Recopa Sudamericana|2014]]\n\n===International===\n\n'''Brazil'''<ref name=\"Olympics\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/ronaldinho_prs205864/person.shtml|title=Ronaldinho Prize List|publisher=Eurosport}}</ref>\n*[[Copa Am\u00e9rica]]: [[1999 Copa Am\u00e9rica|1999]]\n*[[FIFA World Cup]]: [[2002 FIFA World Cup Final|2002]]\n*[[FIFA Confederations Cup]]: [[2005 FIFA Confederations Cup Final|2005]]\n*[[FIFA U-17 World Championship]]: [[1997 FIFA U-17 World Championship|1997]]\n*[[Football at the Summer Olympics|Olympic Bronze Medal]]: [[Football at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|2008]]\n*[[CONMEBOL Pre-Olympic Tournament]]: [[2000 CONMEBOL Pre-Olympic Tournament|2000]]\n\n===Individual===\n* [[FIFA Confederations Cup records and statistics#Awards|FIFA Confederations C